Hazelnut Torte
via via Judy Heumann?

6 eggs, separated
1/4 tsp salt
1 cup sugar
2 cups ground, toasted hazelnuts
1/4 cup cake crumbs
1 tsp baking powder
grated lemon or orange rind
1 tsp rum or liquor
(Add 2 tbsp more liquid)
1 pint whipping cream

Thorougly grease and flour 2 8" layer cake pans.  Beat egg whites with salt
until peaks form.  Very gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until thick.  Set
aside.

Beat yolks until thick and add rum and remaining sugar.

Separately, mix ground nuts mixed with crumbs, baking powder, and rind.  Add to
egg yolk mixture.

Fold in egg whites completely.

Pour into pans and bake for 30 minutes at 350F or until cake springs back in the
center.

Remove from oven and let cool for 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

Whip 1 pint of whipping cream with confectioner's sugar.  Place one layer on a
serving platter, spread with raspberry jam, then cover with whipped cream.
Place second layer on top and repeat with jam and whip cream.

Decorate the top with ground nuts.